<Link id="l00235" /><CodeLine lineNumber="235"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Provides lookup on an on disk hash table.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00236" /><CodeLine lineNumber="236"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00237" /><CodeLine lineNumber="237"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This needs an \\c Info that handles reading values from the hash table&#39;s</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00238" /><CodeLine lineNumber="238"><Highlight kind="comment">/// payload and computes the hash for a given key. This should provide the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00239" /><CodeLine lineNumber="239"><Highlight kind="comment">/// following interface:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00240" /><CodeLine lineNumber="240"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="246"><Highlight kind="comment">///   typedef ExampleKey external&#95;key&#95;type; // The type to pass to find().</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><Highlight kind="comment">///   typedef uint32&#95;t hash&#95;value&#95;type; // The type the hash function returns.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><Highlight kind="comment">///   typedef uint32&#95;t offset&#95;type; // The type for offsets into the table.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><Highlight kind="comment">///   /// Compare two keys for equality.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="251"><Highlight kind="comment">///   static bool EqualKey(internal&#95;key&#95;type &amp;Key1, internal&#95;key&#95;type &amp;Key2);</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="253"><Highlight kind="comment">///   static hash&#95;value&#95;type ComputeHash(internal&#95;key&#95;type &amp;IKey);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00254" /><CodeLine lineNumber="254"><Highlight kind="comment">///   /// Translate from the semantic type of a key in the hash table to the</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00261" /><CodeLine lineNumber="261"><Highlight kind="comment">///   static std::pair&lt;offset&#95;type, offset&#95;type&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00474" /><CodeLine lineNumber="474"><Highlight kind="normal">            <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#ae6c58c37f5229487e86ce915afe1ba12">endian::readNext&lt;uint16&#95;t, llvm::endianness::little&gt;</a>(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/targetlibraryinfo-cpp/#aca185e6d0e9f423dbb24440206454872a11dbf501abf829b3ab7049c2d3a8a053">Ptr</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00477" /><CodeLine lineNumber="477"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Determine the length of the key and the data.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
